I name him Holypikle.<br>
<br>
This name touches upon a joke with some RL friends who play EQ that somewhere out there, there is a Great Holy Pickle who will defeat Boomba the Big, who has enslaved Pickles across Norrath and sells them from his slaveblock in Freeport.<br>
<br>
I was quite tickled to name a character Holypikle. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Tonight, I was approaching level 5 with my Pikle Gnome and I received a tell from a GM....  &quot;Greetings Holypikle.  Your name violates the naming policy and I will be changing it momentarily.  You will have seven days to petition and change your name.&quot;<br>
<br>
Seconds later my name was abruptly changed to the very boring Picaron.<br>
<br>
I responded to the GMs tell and did all I could to be polite while inquiring why my name was a violation.  She said that &quot;holy&quot; could not be in my first name.  &quot;Okay but I can have Holypikle as my surname then when I level to 20?&quot;  &quot;No you cannot have holy in any part of your name.&quot;<br>
<br>
I then responded again that there was already a guild on the server called &quot;Legend of the Holy Blade&quot; and was that a violation too?  <br>
<br>
No response.<br>
<br>
Finally she said &quot;Would you like your name change, Picaron?&quot;<br>
<br>
Me:  &quot;Yes, I would very much like to have Holypikle back.&quot; <br>
<br>
GM:  &quot;This conversation is over.  You were given the option to change your name, but you chose to talk back and be rude.  The ability to petition for a name change has been removed.  Good day Picaron.&quot;<br>
<br>
I sent her several tells saying that I did not feel I was being rude, I was only trying to understand why the name made it past the generator and why it was in violation but a guild tag with &quot;holy&quot; in it was not.  She never responded again.  (Can we say 'BITCH!')  Actually she either made herself invis or logged.<br>
<br>
I TRY to respect GMs because I know they were once players just trying to have fun like me, and they put up with a lot of crap from people... but I am not sure how I feel about this.  It certainly causes a loss of faith to some extent.  <br>
<br>
I relayed my conversation with the GM in /ooc and many other players said they had seen LOTS of characters on other servers with &quot;holy&quot; in their name.  I was tempted to log off and create 6 other characters with &quot;holy&quot; in their name somewhere, but decided against it to avoid a 7-day ban.<br>
<br>
